<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFC5B95DB53E05C09" box="[914,946,1017,1042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="25.0">25</number>
: 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFC7F95DB53855C09" box="[950,983,1017,1042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="29.0">29</number>
: 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFC1295DB53AE5C09" box="[987,1020,1017,1042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="20.0">20</number>
: 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFBC995DB544F5C09" box="[1024,1053,1017,1042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="13.0">13</number>
: 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFBE895DB54625C09" box="[1057,1072,1017,1042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="9.0">9</number>
. 
<emphasis id="B19236593E34AD0CFBF695DB54D25C09" bold="true" box="[1087,1152,1017,1042]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Wing</emphasis>
: brown infuscated, dark brown in anterior half between costa and M, veins dark brown; basal section of M shorter than distal section; R 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFA4D920E55D95C21" box="[1412,1419,1068,1082]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="3.0">3</number>
+ 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFA5D920E55CE5C21" box="[1428,1436,1068,1082]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="4.0">4</number>
and M strongly convergent in apical third; M joining costa anteriad of apex; CuAx ratio: 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFBBE926654CF5C46" box="[1143,1181,1092,1117]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="0.5">0.5</number>
; RMx ratio: 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFAE2926755035C46" box="[1323,1361,1093,1117]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="4.2">4.2</number>
; lower calypter whitish, with black setae; halter stem brown, knob yellow. 
<emphasis id="B19236593E34AD0CFC57924A54405C9A" bold="true" box="[926,1042,1128,1153]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Abdomen</emphasis>
: dark metallic green shining, with black hairs and setae; tergite 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFE2192AF51A45CBF" box="[488,502,1165,1188]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="7.0">7</number>
dark brown, tergite 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFD2B92AF52A25CBE" box="[738,752,1165,1189]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="8.0">8</number>
metallic green. Hypopygium (
<figureCitation id="1BDDF6CE3E34AD0CFB9892AE54C85CBE" box="[1105,1178,1164,1189]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,249,709,731]" captionTargetBox="[158,1424,205,683]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[150,1436,193,688]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hercostomus ibericus sp. nov.: A, cercus, lateral; B, hypopygium lateral (cercus removed). Aed = aedeagus; Apvl = apicoventral epandrial lobe; Hyp = hypandrium; Dsur = dorsal arm of surstylus; Vsur = ventral arm of surstylus (scale bar = 0.1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/238351/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
Figs 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFB4592AF54C85CBE" box="[1164,1178,1165,1189]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A–B): epandrium dark brown; cercus greyish-white, apical border brownish infuscated; hypandrium pale white, epandrial lobes and surstyli brown. Cercus twice as long as wide, with claw-like subapical seta, and with setae on ventral border as long as diameter of cercus; apv lobe with long, projecting basoventral seta and 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFB8D92DA54005D0B" box="[1092,1106,1272,1296]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="2.0">2</number>
small apical setae. 
<emphasis id="B19236593E34AD0CFAF492DA55C65D0A" bold="true" box="[1341,1428,1272,1297]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Female</emphasis>
: unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CBFCB9C03E34AD0CFF0E9362543B5D42" box="[199,1129,1344,1369]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8359EA4B3E34AD0CFF0E9362543B5D42" blockId="3.[151,1437,258,1513]" box="[199,1129,1344,1369]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis id="B19236593E34AD0CFF0E936251145D42" bold="true" box="[199,326,1344,1369]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name refers to the Iberian Peninsula where the species was found.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="CBFCB9C03E34AD0CFF0E934651685DF2" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8359EA4B3E34AD0CFF0E934651685DF2" blockId="3.[151,1437,258,1513]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">
<emphasis id="B19236593E34AD0CFF0E934651665D66" bold="true" box="[199,308,1380,1405]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="44E691C83E34AD0CFD47934753735D67" box="[654,801,1381,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B19236593E34AD0CFD47934753735D67" box="[654,801,1381,1404]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Hercostomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group IV according to 
<bibRefCitation id="E77797BA3E34AD0CFBF2934655475D66" author="Stackelberg" box="[1083,1301,1380,1405]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" refString="Stackelberg, A. (1933) 29. Dolichopodidae. In: Die Fliegen der Palaearktischen Region, 4 (5), Lief. 71, 65 - 128." type="journal article" year="1933">
Stackelberg (
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFB189347555F5D66" box="[1233,1293,1381,1405]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="1933.0">1933</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, with black femora and white or yellow postocular setae. In the Palaearctic key (
<bibRefCitation id="E77797BA3E34AD0CFC4793AA54E95DBB" author="Negrobov" box="[910,1211,1416,1441]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" refString="Negrobov, O. P. &amp; Nechay, N. A. (2009) New species of the genus Hercostomus Loew, 1857 (Diptera, Dolichopodidae) with key of the Palaearctic species of the IV group. Bulletin of Moscow Society of Naturalists, Biological Series, 114 (5), 84 - 87. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="2009">
Negrobov &amp; Nechay 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFBB693AA54E95DBB" box="[1151,1211,1416,1440]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="44E691C83E34AD0CFB0493AB551B5DBB" box="[1229,1353,1416,1440]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ibericus">
<emphasis id="B19236593E34AD0CFB0493AB551B5DBB" box="[1229,1353,1416,1440]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">H. ibericus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
runs to 
<taxonomicName id="44E691C83E34AD0CFF5E938F51BD5DDE" authority="Negrobov, 1976" authorityName="Negrobov" authorityYear="1976" box="[151,495,1452,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albibarbus">
<emphasis id="B19236593E34AD0CFF5E938F51615DDF" box="[151,307,1452,1476]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">H. albibarbus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E77797BA3E34AD0CFEF3938E51BD5DDE" author="Negrobov" box="[314,495,1452,1477]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" refString="Negrobov, O. P. (1976) New species of Dolichopodidae from the Mongolian People's Republic. Nasekomye Mongolii, 4, 501 - 508. [in Russian]" type="journal article" year="1976">
Negrobov, 
<number id="352EF86C3E34AD0CFE7E938E51BD5DDE" box="[439,495,1452,1477]" pageId="3" pageNumber="128" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingCountry id="FBF1AADB3E34AD0CFD6E938E534A5DDE" box="[679,792,1452,1477]" name="Mongolia" pageId="3" pageNumber="128">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
. Both species can be separated by the characters given in the key below.
</paragraph>
